For Frontend Applications

1. Assumption
Assuming you have 2 containers running. 
one is serving ui and other is serving api. 
one is running on container 7001 (ui) and other is running 7002 (api).

2. Installing Nginx on Ubuntu 
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y nginx
sudo systemctl start nginx
sudo systemctl enable nginx

3. DNS  Mapping (Add this A record) 
x.tech  →  YOUR_SERVER_IP

4. Nginx config (sudo nano /etc/nginx/sites-available/x.tech)

server {
    server_name x.tech;

    location / {
        proxy_pass http://localhost:7001;
        proxy_http_version 1.1;
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $remote_addr;
    }

    location /api/ {
        proxy_pass http://localhost:7002/;
        proxy_http_version 1.1;
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $remote_addr;
    }
}
5. Enable site
sudo ln -s /etc/nginx/sites-available/x.tech \
           /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/

6. Test & reload
sudo nginx -t
sudo systemctl reload nginx


7. SSL Certificate After Domain Mapping 
sudo certbot --nginx -d x.tech
